Interface AHCatEntriesPersistence

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.liferay.portal.service.persistence.BasePersistence<AHCatEntries>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AHCatEntriesPersistenceImpl

    public interface AHCatEntriesPersistence
extends com.liferay.portal.service.persistence.BasePersistence<AHCatEntries>
    The persistence interface for the a h cat entries service.

    Caching information and settings can be found in portal.properties

    Author:
    Brian Wing Shun Chan
    See Also:
    AHCatEntriesPersistenceImpl, AHCatEntriesUtil

      • findBycat

        List<AHCatEntries> findBycat(long catId,
                           int start,
                           int end)
                             throws com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException
        Returns a range of all the a h cat entrieses where catId = ?.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil.ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from AHCatEntriesModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        catId - the cat ID
        start - the lower bound of the range of a h cat entrieses
        end - the upper bound of the range of a h cat entrieses (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of matching a h cat entrieses
        Throws:
        SystemException - if a system exception occurred
